newsitem.title: USA: U.S. Plains fed cattle trade quiet - feedlots.
newsitem.headline: U.S. Plains fed cattle trade quiet - feedlots.

text.p: U.S. Plains feedlot cattle markets were quiet early, with no reported sales following this week's activity, which reportedly cleaned up most showlists, feedlot sources said.

A few pens of cattle were still offered at $66.00 to $67.00 per cwt, but cattle feeders did not expect to see any more sales. No bids were reported but they were expected at $64.00 to $65.00 if they surfaced.
Activity was expected light next week because of the Christmas holiday on Wednesday, but prices could bump higher if pipeline supplies get low, sources said.
